---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import TelemetryGrid from '@/components/telemetry/TelemetryGrid.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="My Story">
  <nav class="paddock-override-nav">
    <a href="/" class="return-wall">← PIT WALL</a>
    <div class="nav-title">DRIVER BIOGRAPHY</div>
  </nav>

  <main class="story-viewport">
    <article class="paddock-article">
      <header class="article-header">
        <h1>Driver Profile</h1>
        <p class="summary">The route through Bangladesh, China, and the United States that shaped the systems I build today.</p>
        <div class="t-wrap">
          <TelemetryGrid 
            updated={new Date().toLocaleDateString()}
            status="live"
            stack="Bangladesh, China, USA"
            link="#"
            linkLabel="VERIFIED"
          />
        </div>
      </header>

      <div class="prose">
        <h2>Origins</h2>
        <p>I grew up in Bangladesh and moved to China alone at 16 on a full scholarship to a UWC. Living independently pushed me to understand systems and self-reliance early. I later moved to a small 8,000-person town in Iowa for college, experiencing an entirely different scale of community.</p>

        <h2>Career</h2>
        <p>My professional career spans asset management, sovereign wealth advisory, and data engineering. I’ve worked with BlackRock, Mayo Clinic, and SkyBridge Capital, learning how institutional capital flows and where inefficiencies hide.</p>
        
        <h2>Current Lap</h2>
        <p>I am currently living in Tampa, Florida, and working at Dasseti as a Solutions Engineer. Across all my roles, my focus remains the same: building resilient, scalable tools that solve high-leverage problems. The rest of my time is spent reading, writing, and watching F1 or cricket.</p>

        <hr />

        <h3>Interests</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Cricket:</strong> A lifelong obsession. The strategy and pacing of a test match taught me patience.</li>
          <li><strong>Books:</strong> Constant studying of finance, biographies, and technical systems.</li>
          <li><strong>Formula 1:</strong> Engineering pushed to its breaking point. There is an absolute truth to the stopwatch.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .paddock-override-nav { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; padding: 2rem; font-family: var(--font-mono); }
  .return-wall { color: var(--muted); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .nav-title { color: var(--pitlane-white); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.15em; }
  
  .story-viewport { min-height: 100vh; background: var(--paddock-black); }
  .paddock-article { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 2rem 6rem; }
  
  .article-header { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--carbon); padding-bottom: 3rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; }
  .article-header h1 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(3rem, 5vw, 4rem); margin: 0 0 1rem; color: var(--pitlane-white); line-height: 1.1; }
  .summary { font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 2rem; line-height: 1.6; }
  .t-wrap { max-width: 600px; }
  
  .prose { font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 1.15rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--text); }
  .prose h2 { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 1.1rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-top: 4rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--warning-amber); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--graphite); padding-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .prose h3 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1.8rem; margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--pitlane-white); }
  .prose p { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .prose ul { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  .prose li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .prose hr { border: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--graphite); margin: 3rem 0; }
</style>
